The '''1999 Monte Carlo Open''' was a men's [[tennis]] tournament played on [[Clay court|outdoor clay courts]]. It was the 93rd edition of the [[Monte Carlo Masters|Monte Carlo Open]], and was part of the [[ATP Masters Series|ATP Super 9]] of the [[1999 ATP Tour]]. It took place at the [[Monte Carlo Country Club]] in [[Roquebrune-Cap-Martin]], France, near [[Monte Carlo]], [[Monaco]], from 19 April through 25 April 1999.
Thirteenth-seeded [[Gustavo Kuerten]] won the singles title.
==Finals== ===Singles=== {{main|1999 Monte Carlo Open – Singles}} {{flagicon|BRA}} [[Gustavo Kuerten]] defeated {{flagicon|CHL}} [[Marcelo Ríos]], 6–4, 2–1, retired *It was Gustavo Kuerten's 1st title of the year, and his 4th overall. It was his 1st Masters title of the year, and overall.
===Doubles=== {{main|1999 Monte Carlo Open – Doubles}} {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Olivier Delaître]] / {{flagicon|GBR}} [[Tim Henman]] defeated {{flagicon|CZE}} [[Jiří Novák]] / {{flagicon|CZE}} [[David Rikl]], 6–2, 6–3
