{{Infobox film | name = My Seven Sons | image = | image size = | caption = Russian | director = [[Tofig Tagizadeh]] | producer = [[Azerbaijanfilm]] | writer = [[Yusif Samedoglu]] | narrator = | starring = [[Hasan Mammadov]], [[Anvar Hasanov]], [[Hasanagha Turabov]] | music = [[Khayyam Mirzazadeh]] | cinematography = Rasim Ismayilov | editing = | distributor = | released = {{film date|1970}} | runtime = 90 min. | country = [[Soviet Union]] | language = [[Azerbaijani language|Azerbaijani]] | budget = | gross = }}
'''''My Seven Sons''''' ({{lang-az|Yeddi Oğul İstərəm}}) is a 1970 [[Azerbaijan]]i [[drama film]]. The film plot is written by Yusif Samedoglu based on his father poet [[Samed Vurgun]]'s ''The Komsomol Poem'' which is about the events of 1920's and the Soviet overtaking of Azerbaijan.
The title "Yeddi Oğul İstərəm" derives from Azerbaijani folklore clause ''Yeddi Oğul İstərəm, Bircə Dənə Qız Gəlin'' (meaning "I'd like seven sons and just one daughter"), usually said during the weddings, when the groom comes to the bride's house to pick her up. The movie was shot for the 50th anniversary of establishment of Soviet power in Azerbaijan.<ref>{{Cite web | last = | first = | title = 7 OĞUL İSTƏRƏM | url= http://www.kinozal.az/site/?name=kinoview&kino_id=11 | accessdate = 28 June 2010 }}</ref>
==Plot== This lyrical psychological film is about commitment to the [[Bolshevik revolution]] and its victory. The story is about seven youth who sacrifice everything for the good of people.<ref>{{Cite web | last = | first = | title = 7 OĞUL İSTƏRƏM | url= http://www.kinozal.az/site/?name=kinoview&kino_id=11 | accessdate = 28 June 2010 }}</ref> They travel through the villages during the takeover of Azerbaijan by Bolsheviks in order to establish and strengthen the Soviet power. Events develop in Peykanli village.<ref>{{Cite news | last = Muradli | first = Khayale | title = 40 ilin "Yeddi oğul"u | pages = | newspaper = Lent | location = Baku | date = 21 April 2010 | url = http://www.lent.az/news.php?id=28101 | accessdate = 28 June 2010}}</ref>
==Cast== *[https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Draft:Gasan_Mamedov?markasread=139151069 Gasan Mamedov] as Bakhtiyar * [[Anvar Hasanov]] as Jalal * [[Elchin Mammadov]] as Mirpasha * [[Abdul Mahmudov]] as Gasim * [[Shahmar Alakbarov]] as Gazanfar * [[Rafig Azimov]] as Shahsuvar * [[Alasgar Ibrahimov]] as Zalimoglu * [[Hasanagha Turabov]] as Geray bey * [[Ismayil Osmanli]] as Kalantar * [[Zemfira Ismayilova]] as Humay * [[Hamlet Khanizadeh]] as Gizir
